18/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Four soldiers were killed and three others injured Monday (August 17th) when a grenade exploded during a training session in the eastern province of Elazig, security officials announced. The device blew up in the hands of one of the soldiers, who was on patrol in the Karakocan region.
Another explosion killed one worker and injured 28 others Monday at a fireworks factory in northwest Turkey, near the town of Hendek, in Sakarya province. (Reuters, NTV, CNN Turk, AFP - 17/08/09)
